         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Specialist Independent review of technical and strategic work on site decommissioning and remediation, integrated waste management, spent fuels and nuclear materials — multi supplier framework</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>2017/S 157-325538</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="73200000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Projects under the framework are expected to fall under the following areas:</P>
               <P>— Providing specialist support in formulating, developing and underpinning NDA's strategy across all strategy themes — Independent peer-review of technical documents, plans, programmes of work and projects under other frameworks, e.g. DRP,</P>
               <P>— Assist NDA with technology management and associated plans and procedures,</P>
               <P>— Assist NDA in coordinating and managing technical and strategic meetings, workshops and forums,</P>
               <P>— Assist NDA to develop scopes of work, e.g. Invitation to Tender (ITT) documents for competition under other frameworks (mostly DRP),</P>
               <P>— Support to technical assessment of tender responses to ITTs and deliverables,</P>
               <P>— Desk based strategic assessments where they do not belong under the scope of DRP framework,</P>
               <P>— Experimental work is not in the scope of this framework.</P>
               <P>Contract value estimated to be 2 000 000 GBP over 4 years (24+12+12 months).</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_RANGE_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">
               <LOW>1.00</LOW>
               <HIGH>2000000.00</HIGH>
            </VAL_RANGE_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKD11"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Examples of type of activities and scope associated with each of the areas could include, but are not limited to,the following:</P>
                  <P>1. Site decommissioning and remediation:</P>
                  <P>— Secretary to the nuclear Industry Group for Land Quality inc. support the interaction of the group withstakeholders,</P>
                  <P>— Technical project manager to facilitate the development and delivery of DRP projects.</P>
                  <P>Integrated Waste Management:</P>
                  <P>— Review of Radioactive Waste Management Fora.</P>
                  <P>2. Spent Fuels:</P>
                  <P>— Development of road-maps for Oxide, Magnox and Exotic spent fuel R&amp;D,</P>
                  <P>— Support in coordinating and managing technical meetings and forums on spent fuel management,</P>
                  <P>— Independent review of R&amp;D deliverables.</P>
                  <P>3. Nuclear Materials:</P>
                  <P>— Support to NDA work on uranics and plutonium disposition,</P>
                  <P>— Development and review of technical road-maps on Plutonium disposition options,</P>
                  <P>— Independent review of technical documents on Plutonium disposition options.</P>
                  <P>4. Research and Development:</P>
                  <P>— Independent review of DRP framework contractors' deliverables,</P>
                  <P>— Review and analysis of site license companies TBuRD submissions (e.g. annual technical reports, R &amp; Dtables, technology maps, process wiring diagrams).</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_QUALITY>
                  <AC_CRITERION>Technical</AC_CRITERION>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>70</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_QUALITY>
               <AC_PRICE>
                  <AC_WEIGHTING>30</AC_WEIGHTING>
               </AC_PRICE>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
